rules.ruleString: Must be enrolled in course version {3881}
Must have passed 2 (I/W) units in {BEH4100, BEH4200}

description: This unit aims to increase student understanding of theoretical and methodological aspects of research in community-based emergency health and to develop their analytic, research and communication skills. Students will undertake guided studies in research methodology and complete a supervised research project with the aim of developing both discipline specific and generic research skills
faculty: Faculty of Medicine, Nursing and Health Sciences
